{
  "texts": [
    "More specifically, K-Planes does this by projecting ray samples (containing (x, t)) into 6 feature planes, three representing static space and three representing dynamic space.",
    "The inputs are normalized between [0, N], projected onto the feature planes and bi-linearly interpolated among varying scales (i.e.",
    "coarse and fine features).",
    "To decode the features, attaining (c, σ), element-wise multiplication is used to recover a final feature vector which is passed into a feature decoder (for explicit representation) or small MLP (for implicit representation).",
    "LeGendre et al. (2022) accomplishes image correction for ICVFX using LED walls to project virtual background by first applying two matrices, M and N = MQ -1 to the outof-camera-frustum and in-camera-frustum, respectively, where M and N represents a 3× 3 pre-correction matrix."
  ]
}